title.$t: Redeafination (Deaf Dance) at WTMW 2013 - Wherever You Will Go

media$title.$t: Redeafination (Deaf Dance) at WTMW 2013 - Wherever You Will Go

media$description.$t:
"Who will be there to take my place when I'm gone?"
A dance dedication to all parents, caregivers and teachers of loved ones with special needs and challenges.
Because of your love, we will be strong, wherever we will go.

Choreography: Nix & Gabrielle

Music: Wherever you will go by Charlene Soraia

Dancers:
Geeta (Deaf)
Rebecca (Deaf)
Roseanne (Deaf)
Adelynn (Hearing)
Fern (Hearing)
Gabrielle (Hearing)

This item is presented in Welcome to my World 2013 concert organised by Very Special Arts (VSA) (Singapore). The annual concert is a platform to showcase special needs performing arts groups and is a yearly gathering of family, schools and friends of the special needs community to celebrate the talents and strengths of the special ones.

============================

About Redeafination:

Formed in 2008, Redeafination is a self-funded, independent hip hop dance group for the Deaf. Through the universal language of dance, we seek to promote deaf awareness as well as to nurture and develop performing arts talents within the Deaf community.

The crew is made of a majority of Deaf dancers.

Website:
http://www.redeafination.com/

Facebook:
http://www.facebook.com/redeafination

Twitter:
http://www.twitter.com/redeafination

Email:
redeafination@gmail.com

About VSA (Singapore):
Very Special Arts Singapore (VSA Singapore) is a charity launched in September 1993 to provide people with disabilities with opportunities to access the arts for rehabilitation and social integration.

title.$t: Redeafination + Fun Forest at VSA WTMW 2012 (Deaf Dance)

media$title.$t: Redeafination + Fun Forest at VSA WTMW 2012 (Deaf Dance)

media$description.$t:
Redeafination performs for the 4th year running at "Welcome to My World 2012", a concert by people with disabilities, organized by Very Special Arts (Singapore) on 02 June 2012.

This year, Redeafination collaborates with another Deaf dance crew, 
Fun Forest, from Hong Kong. With the help and support of the public, 
both crews managed to raise sufficient funds that made the project possible.

Witness their collaboration - Made from a week's worth of intensive training and the bonds between the two crews that were strengthened along the way.

Thank you for making this possible. :)

title.$t: Deaf Groove Ignition 2011

media$title.$t: Deaf Groove Ignition 2011

media$description.$t:
Deaf Groove Ignition (DGI) started in 2010 with the objective to provide hip hop dance training exposure to Deaf students who currently has very little or no learning opportunity in this arena. 

In our pilot year in 2010, 11 Deaf benefitted from the workshop. Amongst these, 6 are currently pursuing their dance passion in Redeafination as performing members. 4 others have been active participating in our subsequent specialized courses and events.

DGI is back again in 2011!

WHEN :: 11,12 June 2011, 2-5pm
WHERE :: Pathlight School 
FOR :: Deaf Students Age 12-30
BY :: Redeafination
FEES :: Waived for Students

For full details please visit http://www.redeafination.com/dgi

title.$t: Redeafination @ Danzation 2011 - Opening Item Video

media$title.$t: Redeafination @ Danzation 2011 - Opening Item Video

media$description.$t:
This video was presented prior to Redeafination's (RDF) opening item at Danzation 2011 (the first of 3 items involving RDF).

Danzation marks the end of a year long collaboration between RDF and NRA to bring the Deaf and Hearing dance world together through a cultural exchange program that promotes real hands on awareness of the Deaf culture in Singapore amongst the NRA dancers/choreographers.

Danzation also featured for the first time, a unique blend of hip hop dance, fused with the Deaf performing art of song signing.

title.$t: Signmark - Our Life (Deaf Rap)

media$title.$t: Signmark - Our Life (Deaf Rap)

media$description.$t:
Introducing Signmark - Deaf Finnish rap artist. 

He describes his music as being party hip hop that takes a stand. Born into a signing family, he feels that society should not treat the Deaf as disabled people but as a linguistic minority with their own culture and history

All rights to the music video and song are the property of Signmark.

We are just trying to spread the message, and to subtitle it so folks can see the validity of Sign Rap as a Deaf performing art form.

To support Signmark and his other works go to http://www.signmark.biz/site/en/home

content.$t:

media$title.$t: Redeafination (Deaf Dance) - Celebrates National Dance Day with America

media$description.$t:
Dance is a universal language. And we love to dance!

Redeafination celebrates America's National Dance Day - a community initiative by Dizzy Feet foundation, launched on So You Think You Can Dance, in support of dance education and physical fitness

Choreography: Napoleon and Tabitha

=======
About Redeafination:

Redeafination is a self-funded, independent hip hop dance group for the Deaf, 
Through the universal language of dance, we seek to promote deaf awareness as well as to nurture and develop performing arts talents within the Deaf community.

The crew is made up of a mix of Deaf and Hearing dancers 

Website:
http://redeafination.wordpress.com/

Facebook:
http://www.facebook.com/redeafination

Twitter:
http://www.twitter.com/redeafination

Email:
redeafination@gmail.com

title.$t: Redeafination - Deaf Song Sign Dance - Make You Feel My Love

media$title.$t: Redeafination - Deaf Song Sign Dance - Make You Feel My Love

media$description.$t:
Redeafination performs our debut Song Sign Dance item - "Make You Feel My Love" at "Welcome to My World 09" - a Concert by People with Disabilities organized by Very Special Arts (Singapore) on 28 March 2009

============================
Item Synopsis:
Love is often hard to express in words. Is there someone you care for but have not told them so? 3 dancers decide to say it in their own unique way through a beautiful fusion of sign language and dance. While they make you feel their love, remember to let your loved ones know how you feel soon. Maybe now.

Choreography: Nix

Song Sign Advisor: Hina

Dancers:
Angeline (Hearing Impaired)
Geeta (Hearing Impaired)
Fern (Hearing)

Make-Up & Hair by:
Style To Perfection (STP)
For enquries, please contact Furbee
Email: Styletoperfection@live.com.sg
Mobile: 94813320

============================
About Redeafination:

Redeafination is a self-funded, independent hip hop dance group for the Deaf, 
Through the universal language of dance, we seek to promote deaf awareness as well as to nurture and develop performing arts talents within the Deaf community.

The crew is made up of a mix of Deaf and Hearing dancers 

Website:
http://redeafination.wordpress.com/

Facebook:
http://www.facebook.com/redeafination

Twitter:
http://www.twitter.com/redeafination

Email:
redeafination@gmail.com

About VSA (Singapore):
Very Special Arts Singapore (VSA Singapore) is a charity launched in September 1993 to provide people with disabilities with opportunities to access the arts for rehabilitation and social integration.

media$title.$t: Redeafination - Deaf Dance @ NTU Dancetitude '09 (Full Item)

media$description.$t:
Redeafination and Legend collaborate together to perform a guest item for NTU Modern Jazz Concert - Dancetitude 2009.

Please feel free to leave a comment or feedback.

The original video-docu segment can be viewed here:
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D9UdsxUvacg

=======================================
Item Synopsis:
A group of defunct glamour dolls lay abandoned, forgotten. A new surge of energy strikes them and re-ignites their former glories. As they gradually discover what this godsent is, they indulge and celebrate their regained glamour. But the gift is only a catalyst and the energy quickly dissipates. Only those who possess the real passion deep within themselves can continue to fuel the fire of life, and survive the journey.

Choreographers:
Mornin, Jason, Nix

Dancers:
Jason (Redeafination)
Nix (Redeafination)
Hina (Redeafination)
Geeta (Redeafination)
Donny (Redeafination)
Jonathan (Redeafination)
Roseanne (Redeafination)
Linghong (Redeafination)
Mornin (Legend)
Jade (Legend)
Missy (Legend)
Huishan (Legend)
Yvonne (Legend)
Hugo (Legend)

Music:
VIP - Big Bang
Heavens Reject - Iron Soul
Boiler - Maniac
Poker Face - Lady Gaga

Make-Up & Hair by:
Style To Perfection (STP)
